casebody.data:
Robert W. Millette v. Frederick G. Reincke, Warden, Connecticut State Prison Argued February 6 decided February 6, 1968 Submitted January 26

decided February 6, 1968

Thomas F. Wall, state’s attorney, for the appellee (defendant). Arnold II. Klau, special public defender, for the appellant (plaintiff). Arnold II. Klau, in support of the motion.

The motion by the defendant to dismiss the appeal from the Superior Court in Hartford County is granted unless the plaintiff files his brief on or before March 15, 1968.

The motion by the plaintiff to have the appellant’s brief in the case of Gould v. Reincke, 155 Conn. 703, 236 A.2d 916, treated as his brief in his appeal from the Superior Court in Hartford County is denied.
